# Logs

# This command displays system log entries from the past hour that are classified as errors or more severe levels (such as critical, alert, or emergency).
sudo journalctl -p err --since "1 hour ago"

# sudo: Grants administrative privileges, often needed to access all journal entries.
# journalctl: The command to query and display logs from systemd's journal.
# -p err: Filters logs by priority (or "priority level") to show only messages at the "err" level and above (i.e., err, crit, alert, emerg).
# --since "1 hour ago": Restricts output to entries from the last hour.

